<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="448" pageId="2" pageNumber="447" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,308,713]" pageId="2" pageNumber="447">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,290,344,367]" pageId="2" pageNumber="447">Description.</emphasis>
Vertex brownish yellow, with large irregular central black spot (
<figureCitation box="[1009,1075,344,367]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1984,2006]" captionTargetBox="[230,1359,779,1953]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[220,1366,767,1960]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Salka acicula sp. nov.: 1, Head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, Abdominal apodemes; 3, Pygofer, lateral view; 4, Style, lateral view; 5, Aedeagus, lateral view; 6, Aedeagus, ventral view; 7, Connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261203/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="447">
Fig. 
<number box="[1062,1075,344,367]" pageId="2" pageNumber="447" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
). Eyes black (
<figureCitation box="[1238,1304,344,367]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1984,2006]" captionTargetBox="[230,1359,779,1953]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[220,1366,767,1960]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Salka acicula sp. nov.: 1, Head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, Abdominal apodemes; 3, Pygofer, lateral view; 4, Style, lateral view; 5, Aedeagus, lateral view; 6, Aedeagus, ventral view; 7, Connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261203/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="447">
Fig. 
<number box="[1291,1304,344,367]" pageId="2" pageNumber="447" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
). Pronotum blackish brown, with anterior margin and intermediate zone light yellow (
<figureCitation box="[956,1021,378,401]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1984,2006]" captionTargetBox="[230,1359,779,1953]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[220,1366,767,1960]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Salka acicula sp. nov.: 1, Head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, Abdominal apodemes; 3, Pygofer, lateral view; 4, Style, lateral view; 5, Aedeagus, lateral view; 6, Aedeagus, ventral view; 7, Connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261203/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="447">
Fig. 
<number box="[1008,1021,378,401]" pageId="2" pageNumber="447" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
). Scutellum dark, with basal triangles indistinct (
<figureCitation box="[266,329,413,436]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1984,2006]" captionTargetBox="[230,1359,779,1953]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[220,1366,767,1960]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Salka acicula sp. nov.: 1, Head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, Abdominal apodemes; 3, Pygofer, lateral view; 4, Style, lateral view; 5, Aedeagus, lateral view; 6, Aedeagus, ventral view; 7, Connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261203/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="447">
Fig. 
<number box="[316,329,413,436]" pageId="2" pageNumber="447" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
). Face light yellow, without obvious patches. Fore wing brownish yellow, with brochosome field dark brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,308,713]" box="[199,908,482,505]" pageId="2" pageNumber="447">
Male abdominal apodemes slightly exceeding 
<number box="[694,705,482,505]" pageId="2" pageNumber="447" value="3.0">3</number>
rd sternite (
<figureCitation box="[829,895,482,505]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1984,2006]" captionTargetBox="[230,1359,779,1953]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[220,1366,767,1960]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Salka acicula sp. nov.: 1, Head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, Abdominal apodemes; 3, Pygofer, lateral view; 4, Style, lateral view; 5, Aedeagus, lateral view; 6, Aedeagus, ventral view; 7, Connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261203/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="447">
Fig. 
<number box="[879,895,482,505]" pageId="2" pageNumber="447" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,308,713]" pageId="2" pageNumber="447">
<emphasis box="[199,356,516,540]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="447">Male genitalia</emphasis>
: Pygofer dorsal appendage not extended beyond caudal margin of lobe, little curved ventrally, with apex sharp (
<figureCitation box="[286,354,552,575]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1984,2006]" captionTargetBox="[230,1359,779,1953]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[220,1366,767,1960]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Salka acicula sp. nov.: 1, Head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, Abdominal apodemes; 3, Pygofer, lateral view; 4, Style, lateral view; 5, Aedeagus, lateral view; 6, Aedeagus, ventral view; 7, Connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261203/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="447">
Fig. 
<number box="[339,354,552,575]" pageId="2" pageNumber="447" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
). Pygofer ventral appendage long and slim, branched about 
<number box="[1020,1030,552,575]" pageId="2" pageNumber="447" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[1041,1055,552,575]" pageId="2" pageNumber="447" value="3.0">3</number>
distance from apex, dorsal branch long, ventral branch extremely short (
<figureCitation box="[554,619,586,609]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1984,2006]" captionTargetBox="[230,1359,779,1953]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[220,1366,767,1960]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Salka acicula sp. nov.: 1, Head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, Abdominal apodemes; 3, Pygofer, lateral view; 4, Style, lateral view; 5, Aedeagus, lateral view; 6, Aedeagus, ventral view; 7, Connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261203/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="447">
Fig. 
<number box="[604,619,586,609]" pageId="2" pageNumber="447" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate with 
<number box="[873,886,586,609]" pageId="2" pageNumber="447" value="3.0">3</number>
macrosetae on outer surface and row of short setae along upper margin, basal setae of row longer than distal setae (
<figureCitation box="[841,907,621,644]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1984,2006]" captionTargetBox="[230,1359,779,1953]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[220,1366,767,1960]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Salka acicula sp. nov.: 1, Head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, Abdominal apodemes; 3, Pygofer, lateral view; 4, Style, lateral view; 5, Aedeagus, lateral view; 6, Aedeagus, ventral view; 7, Connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261203/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="447">
Fig. 
<number box="[892,907,621,644]" pageId="2" pageNumber="447" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
). Style tapering towards apex (
<figureCitation box="[1243,1310,621,644]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1984,2006]" captionTargetBox="[230,1359,779,1953]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[220,1366,767,1960]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Salka acicula sp. nov.: 1, Head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, Abdominal apodemes; 3, Pygofer, lateral view; 4, Style, lateral view; 5, Aedeagus, lateral view; 6, Aedeagus, ventral view; 7, Connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261203/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="447">
Fig. 
<number box="[1294,1310,621,644]" pageId="2" pageNumber="447" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus wide in lateral view, with pair of small lateral processes arising near midlength of shaft; gonopore apical on ventral surface (
<figureCitation box="[242,339,690,713]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1984,2006]" captionTargetBox="[230,1359,779,1953]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[220,1366,767,1960]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Salka acicula sp. nov.: 1, Head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, Abdominal apodemes; 3, Pygofer, lateral view; 4, Style, lateral view; 5, Aedeagus, lateral view; 6, Aedeagus, ventral view; 7, Connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261203/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="447">
Figs 
<number box="[296,339,690,713]" pageId="2" pageNumber="447" value="5.6">5, 6</number>
</figureCitation>
). Connective Y-shaped, with distinct central lobe (
<figureCitation box="[877,942,690,713]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1984,2006]" captionTargetBox="[230,1359,779,1953]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[220,1366,767,1960]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Salka acicula sp. nov.: 1, Head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, Abdominal apodemes; 3, Pygofer, lateral view; 4, Style, lateral view; 5, Aedeagus, lateral view; 6, Aedeagus, ventral view; 7, Connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261203/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="447">
Fig. 
<number box="[927,942,690,713]" pageId="2" pageNumber="447" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261203/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="447" targetBox="[230,1359,779,1953]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1984,2035]" pageId="2" pageNumber="447">
