</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="448" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,152,417]" pageId="3" pageNumber="448">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,309,256,279]" pageId="3" pageNumber="448">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Chiang &amp; Knight (1990)" authorityName="Chiang &amp; Knight" authorityYear="1990" box="[585,1012,255,279]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Salka" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="448" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fujiwara">
<emphasis box="[585,742,255,279]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="448">Salka fujiwara</emphasis>
Chiang &amp; Knight (
<number box="[946,1004,256,279]" pageId="3" pageNumber="448" value="1990.0">1990</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
, but differs in having the aedeagus with a pair of small processes arising from the middle of the aedeagal shaft laterally (
<figureCitation box="[998,1094,290,313]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1984,2006]" captionTargetBox="[230,1359,779,1953]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[220,1366,767,1960]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Salka acicula sp. nov.: 1, Head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, Abdominal apodemes; 3, Pygofer, lateral view; 4, Style, lateral view; 5, Aedeagus, lateral view; 6, Aedeagus, ventral view; 7, Connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261203/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="448">
Figs 
<number box="[1051,1094,290,313]" pageId="3" pageNumber="448" value="5.6">5, 6</number>
</figureCitation>
); the pygofer ventral appendage bifurcate 
<number box="[252,262,325,348]" pageId="3" pageNumber="448" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[272,286,325,348]" pageId="3" pageNumber="448" value="3.0">3</number>
distance from the apex (
<figureCitation box="[549,614,325,348]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1984,2006]" captionTargetBox="[230,1359,779,1953]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[220,1366,767,1960]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Salka acicula sp. nov.: 1, Head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, Abdominal apodemes; 3, Pygofer, lateral view; 4, Style, lateral view; 5, Aedeagus, lateral view; 6, Aedeagus, ventral view; 7, Connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261203/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="448">
Fig. 
<number box="[599,614,325,348]" pageId="3" pageNumber="448" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
); and the apex of the style long and tapered (
<figureCitation box="[1094,1160,325,348]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1984,2006]" captionTargetBox="[230,1359,779,1953]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[220,1366,767,1960]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Salka acicula sp. nov.: 1, Head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, Abdominal apodemes; 3, Pygofer, lateral view; 4, Style, lateral view; 5, Aedeagus, lateral view; 6, Aedeagus, ventral view; 7, Connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261203/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="448">
Fig. 
<number box="[1144,1160,325,348]" pageId="3" pageNumber="448" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="448" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,152,417]" pageId="3" pageNumber="448">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,327,360,383]" pageId="3" pageNumber="448">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name is derived from the Latin word “ 
<emphasis box="[883,972,359,383]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="448">aciculus</emphasis>
”, referring to the aedeagus with one paired small appendage (
<figureCitation box="[343,440,394,417]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1984,2006]" captionTargetBox="[230,1359,779,1953]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[220,1366,767,1960]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Salka acicula sp. nov.: 1, Head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, Abdominal apodemes; 3, Pygofer, lateral view; 4, Style, lateral view; 5, Aedeagus, lateral view; 6, Aedeagus, ventral view; 7, Connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261203/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="448">
Figs 
<number box="[397,440,394,417]" pageId="3" pageNumber="448" value="5.6">5, 6</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
